<td width="77%" align="center" valign="top" rowspan="6" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!--CONTENT TABLE-->

    <table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		<tr>
			<td align="left" width="50%"></td>
			<td align="right" width="50%"><img align="top" src="../../../images/right.jpg" WIDTH="15" HEIGHT="13"></td>
		</tr>
    </table> </font></big><p><big><font color="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</font></big></p>
    <table border="0" width="85%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
      <table width=60% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=center>

	<font color="#0e024d" face="Arial"><LEFT><big><strong>WIZARD KUNARK SPELL DETAILS - BETA LIST ONLY</strong></big><P>
<small><small>THIS SPELL LIST IS BETA ONLY - DETAILS <U>WILL</U> CHANGE REGULARLY UNTIL THE EXPANSION IS RELEASED, NOTHING IS CONFIRMED.</small></small></LEFT></font>
        <hr size="1" color="#0e042d">
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Name: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Abscond.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Level: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>52.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Mana: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>600.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Class: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Alteration.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Vendor: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Unknown.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Approx Spell Cost: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top'  width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Unknown.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Researchable: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>No.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Type: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top'  width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Personal Teleport Spell (Self Only).</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Actual Effects:</font></small></b></td><td colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Self: Long Range Yonder.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Description:</font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>This spell will teleport you within the zone to a point a great distance from where you are currently located.<P>
It is an upgraded form of Yonder.<P>Casting Time: 7.0 Seconds<br>
Recast Time: 10.0 Seconds</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign= 'top' colspan='2'><br><font face='Arial'><small>Click <b><a href='mailto:grimstaff@castersrealm.com?subject=You need to update info on Abscond - SpellID: 296'>Here</b></a> to report an error in this spells information.</small></font></td></tr>

	<tr>
	    <td>
		
		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><hr size='1'><font face='Arial' color='#0E024D'><b>Transport to safe point and clear hate list</font></b><small><b><font face='arial'color='#0E024D'> -</font></small><font face='arial' color='#800000'><small> Svane Astralsage</b></font></small></TD>
		</TR>

		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><font face='arial'><small>I talked to GZ about this spell in the Verant booth at E3 2000.  He stated that this 
spell and the Evacuate spell both transport the wizard (or entire party in the case of 
Evacuate) to the safe point in the current zone.  In addition, GZ also stated that 
casting this spell clears the hate list for the wiz/party, which keeps the mobs from 
training to the safe point to get the party.

The 600 mana cost for Abscond is intentionally high in order to keep the wizard from 
running back to reengage the mob right away.  For Evacuate, apparently the spell 
has a negative side effect that it actually drains mana from the entire party as well 
as the caster; at least this is what GZ said.

As far as I know this spell isn't dropping yet but hopefully Verant will fix this soon.

Svane Astralsage, Wizard on E'ci

</small></font><BR></TD>
		</TR>
		
		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><hr size='1'><font face='Arial' color='#0E024D'><b>Useless spell</font></b><small><b><font face='arial'color='#0E024D'> -</font></small><font face='arial' color='#800000'><small> Rhad</b></font></small></TD>
		</TR>

		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><font face='arial'><small> While the high mana cost is intended to stop the party from running back and 
re-engaging, it also makes this spell entirely useless.  I obtained this spell by trading 
Inferno Spiral of Al'Kabor to the wizard spell "quest" npc in firiona vie.  It costs 600 
mana, fizzles a LOT (probably due to level) which eats 300 mana per fizzle.  The long 
cast time really makes it impractical to use in battle.  The extremely high mana cost 
sheds serious doubt on where this could possibly be usefull.  If a creature is so 
overpowered that you know you're going to lose with 600 mana left, is there really 
much chance that you will be able to root it out of the way, and cast this spell?  
Given that it takes you to "the zone safe spot" - which anyone that has experienced 
zoning bugs knows is not always safe (player is beneath world, moving them to a 
safe spot You have been slain by Bouncer Hurd!) in ALL cases I would rather use 
something simple like fay gate (similar cast time, 1/4 mana cost, removes you from 
the zone so agro is automaticly cleared) or gate (you cant bind in dungeons, but you 
can bind just outside of them, and i seriously doubt the "safe spot" in a dungeon will 
be anywhere other than the zone-in.)  The location of the safe spots also make this a 
poor choice for travel aid.  For example, the "safe spot" location in dreadlands is 
about 50 feet from the wizard spires - if I need to get to these spires you can be sure 
i'll spend 300 mana for a port or even 150 mana to gate out of zone and 300 mana to 
port back in before i use a 600 mana spell.  This seems to be a case where the 
original idea was good, but it's been made so "anti-exploit" that it now has no use in 
legitimate situations.</small></font><BR></TD>
		</TR>
		
		<TR><TD colspan="3"><hr size='1'></TD></TR>
